- 3.3.0-SNAP4](metadata/org.scalatest/scalatest-featurespec_3/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> ScalaTest FeatureSpec is the ScalaTest module that provides the feature-specification style for organizing tests around features and scenarios. It lets Scala 3 projects write behavior-driven, readable test suites that integrate with ScalaTest's assertions, fixtures, and runner ecosystem.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/org.scalatest/scalatest-featurespec_3/) |\n../6222-8d0a097b/COVERAGE.md:1240:| `org.scalatest:scalatest-flatspec_3` | [3.2.19<br>- 3.3.0-SNAP4](metadata/org.scalatest/scalatest-flatspec_3/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> ScalaTest FlatSpec provides the FlatSpec testing style for ScalaTest, letting Scala developers write behavior-driven tests as flat specifications with it/should or they/should clauses. This Scala 3 JVM artifact supplies synchronous, asynchronous, and fixture-based FlatSpec suite classes that integrate with ScalaTest assertions, tagging, and reporting.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/org.scalatest/scalatest-flatspec_3/) |\n../6222-8d0a097b/COVERAGE.md:1241:| `org.scalatest:scalatest-freespec_2.13` | [3.2.19<br>- 3.3.0-SNAP4](metadata/org.scalatest/scalatest-freespec_2.13/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> ScalaTest FreeSpec provides ScalaTest's FreeSpec style, letting tests be written as nested, descriptive phrases that define a tree of behavior-focused examples. The artifact supplies the synchronous, asynchronous, fixture, and path-oriented FreeSpec classes for Scala 2.13 test suites.</details> | [100.0% (1/1 calls)](stats/org.scalatest/scalatest-freespec_2.13/) |\n../6222-8d0a097b/COVERAGE.md:1242:| `org.scalatest:scalatest-funspec_2.13` | [3.2.19<br>- 3.3.0-SNAP4](metadata/org.scalatest/scalatest-funspec_2.13/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> ScalaTest FunSpec provides the FunSpec style for writing behavior-driven ScalaTest suites with nested describe and it clauses. It includes synchronous, asynchronous, fixture-based, and path-based suite classes that integrate with ScalaTest assertions, tagging, and test lifecycle features.</details> | [100.0% (1/1 calls)](stats/org.scalatest/scalatest-funspec_2.13/) |\n../6222-8d0a097b/COVERAGE.md:1243:| `org.scalatest:scalatest-funspec_3` | [3.2.19<br>- 3.3.0-SNAP4](metadata/org.scalatest/scalatest-funspec_3/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> ScalaTest FunSpec provides the FunSpec style for writing behavior-driven ScalaTest suites with nested describe and it clauses. It includes synchronous, asynchronous, fixture-based, and path-based suite classes that integrate with ScalaTest assertions, tagging, and test lifecycle features.</details> | [100.0% (1/1 calls)](stats/org.scalatest/scalatest-funspec_3/) |\n../6222-8d0a097b/COVERAGE.md:1244:| `org.scalatest:scalatest-funsuite_2.13` | [3.2.19<br>- 3.3.0-SNAP4](metadata/org.scalatest/scalatest-funsuite_2.13/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> ScalaTest FunSuite provides the FunSuite testing style for ScalaTest on the JVM, where tests are registered as named functions rather than discovered as methods. It integrates with ScalaTest's assertions, fixtures, tagging, asynchronous suites, and reporting so Scala projects can write function-oriented unit tests.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/org.scalatest/scalatest-funsuite_2.13/) |\n../6222-8d0a097b/COVERAGE.md:1245:| `org.scalatest:scalatest-funsuite_3` | [3.2.19<br>- 3.3.0-SNAP4](metadata/org.scalatest/scalatest-funsuite_3/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> ScalaTest FunSuite provides the FunSuite testing style for ScalaTest, where each test is registered and executed as a function value. This artifact is the Scala 3 JVM module for that style, including synchronous, asynchronous, and fixture-based FunSuite APIs for Scala test suites.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/org.scalatest/scalatest-funsuite_3/) |\n../6222-8d0a097b/COVERAGE.md:1246:| `org.scalatest:sca